  <p>
    The first part of the project was laying out the scene's structure with
    primitive objects and animations. I decided on four different arcade
    machines that I would model and feature as centerpieces for our statistics.
  </p>
  <p>
    I had a lot of fun doing design research and making
    <a href="https://pin.it/6ZDH85YdT" target="_blank"
      >mood and reference boards</a
    >
    inspired by the vibrant aesthetic of the 90s and early Y2K era. I drew
    heavily from vibrant neon color schemes and funky geometric patterns that
    were commonplace in locations like arcades I visited as a child, and
    yearbook spreads I had in elementary school.
  </p>
</div>

