<div class="side-by-side">
  <p>
    Having primarily used Blender for realistic 3D animation, I wanted to try
    something new for this project and took a deep dive into stylized 3D,
    conducting in-depth research into the Grease Pencil tool. I learned a lot
    from
    <a
      href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=blender+grease+pencil"
      target="_blank"
      >community tutorials on YouTube</a
    >
    and the CG Boost course "Magic Storybook." Drawing on 3D planes was a
    learning curve, but once it clicked with my brain it became second nature.
  </p>
  <p>
    For this project I used an iPad and Apple Pencil directly in Blender via
    Astropad, though the limited screen size left me wanting more. Since it was
    such a fun project to work on, I've since upgraded my setup to a screen
    tablet, and I'm continuing to explore and improve my illustrative style.
  </p>
